 Step 1: Calculate the total amount Jill earns from teaching.
Jill teaches for 35 hours a week at $20/hour.
Total earnings from teaching = 35 hours/week * $20/hour
Step 2: Calculate the total amount Jill earns from being a cheerleader.
Jill coaches for 15 hours a week at $30/hour.
Total earnings from coaching = 15 hours/week * $30/hour
Step 3: Add the two amounts together to get Jill's total annual salary.
Let's solve it:

####

Step 1:
\begin{align*}
& \text{Total earnings from teaching} \\
&= 35 \text{ hours/week} \times \$20/\text{hour} \\
&= \$700/\text{week}
\end{align*}

Step 2:
\begin{align*}
& \text{Total earnings from coaching} \\
&= 15 \text{ hours/week} \times \$30/\text{hour} \\
&= \$450/\text{week}
\end{align*}

Step 3:
\begin{align*}
& \text{Total annual salary} \\
&= \$700/\text{week} + \$450/\text{week} \\
&= \$1150/\text{week}
\end{align*}

Therefore, Jill's annual salary is $1150 per week or $58,500 per year. #### 58500

